dancerctl - like apachectl for perl/Dancer apps
================================================
Small tool that can start/stop/restart Dancer apps

Usage: 

dancerctl [appname] action [environment]

Where:
action      - start/stop/restart. 
              Will start/stop/restart all available apps if no $appname is specified [not implemented now]
environment - usually 'development' or 'production'

Examples under not root user:

dancerctl dancer_app start|stop|restart|status [environment]

Examples under root(!) user: [not implemented]

dancerctl user dancer_app start|stop|restart|status [environment]

dancerctl help
dancerctl setup   [not implemented]
dancerctl update  [not implemented]

Configs (in order of priority DESC)
====================================
~/.dancer/$appname [environment: section]
~/.dancer/$appname [root param]
~/.dancer [not implemented now, may be in future]
/etc/dancer.conf

Config format: YAML for first to and any ini-style (as for now) for /etc/dancder.conf

Config example
===============
/home/user/.dancer/app

# path to app: app -> /home/user/app
path: app

# default environment - useful to set 'development' on developer's laptop during 
# development and 'production' on production server
env: development

# start on startall
# will be used global 'autostart' if not specified.
# can be set as 1 in global and 0 on local to start_all all apps by default and 
# not autostart this app
autostart: 0

production:
  # -l /home/user/app/app.sock
  method: socket
development:
  # -w 1
  workers: 1
  # -l localhost:3002
  method: port
  port: 3002
  # --pid /home/user/app/dev.pid
  pid_name: dev.pid
demo:
  # -l localhost:3999
  port: 3999
  # this will be added to the end of plackup sting
  opt: "--backlog 1024 --max-requests 100"

  
Install
========
Cpanminus and perl 5.10 are required.

cpanm Config::Auto

'dancerctl' was tested under modern version of Ubuntu (11.04). 
Some part (like 'status') may not work under different linuxes and OSes 
(note hardcoded slashes).


